==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-fold.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Transitive verb===
'''to fold''' (''past tense and past participle'' '''folded''')

# to [[bend]] (any thin material, such as paper) over so that it comes in contact with itself.
# to make the proper [[arrangement]] in a thin [[material]] by bending.
#: "You haven't folded the sheets, they're wrong".
# to [[fall over]].
# to give way on a point or in an argument.
# (''poker'') To [[pull out]] of [[bet]]ting
# To [[stir]] gently, with a folding action.
#:'''''Fold''' the egg whites into the batter.''

